-- Indonesia Stock Movers: Aneka Tambang, Bank CIMB Niaga, Timah
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-02-22T03:53:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/indonesia-stock-movers-aneka-tambang-bank-cimb-niaga-timah.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 10:42 a.m. in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index  slid 0.4 percent to 3,988.66,
set for the first decline in four days.  Metal producers:  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM)  , Indonesia’s
second-biggest nickel producer, rose 1 percent to 2,000 rupiah.
 PT Timah (TINS)  , the largest tin maker, gained 1.5 percent to
2,000 rupiah. Nickel futures rose 2.4 percent to $20,230 a
metric ton in  London  yesterday while tin increased 2.9 percent
to $24,190 a ton.  PT Bank CIMB Niaga (BNGA)  , the Indonesian unit of
Malaysia’s CIMB Group Holdings Bhd., climbed 0.9 percent to
1,170 rupiah. CIMB Niaga said 2011 net income rose 28 percent
from a year earlier to 3.2 trillion rupiah ($353 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
